Our DevRel lead @0xThiru presented ERC-8028 at EIP Day during Devconnect Buenos Aires, introducing a new standard that could reshape how AI assets work on Ethereum üßµ 
@0xThiru He explained that ERC-8028 is a semi-fungible token standard designed specifically for onchain AI assets.

Unlike existing standards like ERC-20 or ERC-721, it's engineered to handle the unique requirements of AI. 
@0xThiru The new standard makes use of Data Anchoring Tokens (DAT).

Each DAT contains metadata for identification, categorization, revenue sharing quotas, and proof mechanisms that can integrate ZK proofs or other verification methods. 
@0xThiru Thiru demonstrated a real-world example with Lazbubu, built on @LazAINetwork.

When users interact with Lazbubu, usage is recorded onchain and DAT contributors earn rewards in real-time. 
@0xThiru @LazAINetwork Thiru's presentation showed how ERC-8028 can be used to solve the data alignment problem by creating proper incentives for data contribution.

This lays the foundation for a human-aligned AI economy built on Ethereum infrastructure. 
